name: pasargad tomb of cyrus the great#2
description:
The Tomb of Cyrus, previously known as the Tomb of Suleiman's Mother, is a monument thought to be the tomb of Cyrus the Great, the founder of the ancient Achaemenid Empire. It is located in Pasargadae, an archaeological site in the Fars Province of Iran.
